# Network Fundamentals

TCPDUMP
    sudo tcpdump -d (lists interfaces)
    sudo tcpdump -i interface -nXXvvv (displays verbose well formatted)
    sudo tcpdump -i interface -w file (writes pcap to file)
    sudo tcpdump -r file (reads pcap file)
    sudo tcpdump port xxx or xxx -vnXX (filters traffic to specific port)
   
BPF
    tcpdump {A}[B:C] {D} {E} {F} {G}
    A = Protocol (ether | arp | ip | ip6 | icmp | tcp | udp)
    B = Header Byte offset
    C = Byte Length. Can be 1, 2, or 4 (Default 1)
    D = Bitwise Mask (&)
    E = Operator
    F = Result of Expression
    G = Logical Operator
    
    Bitwise Masking
        

